G-Golf GObject modules are defined in the @code{gobject}
subdirectory, such as @code{(g-golf gobject enum-flags)}.

Where you may load these modules individually, the easiest way to use
G-Golf is to import the @code{gobject} module: it imports and re-exports
the public interface of (oop goops), (system foreign), all G-Golf
support and G-Golf GObject modules:

@lisp
(use-modules (g-golf gobject))
@end lisp

G-Golf GObject low level API modules correspond to a GObject section,
though they might be some exception in the future.


